You should use boolean false instead of 0. This works as expected:
</p>
<pre class="wiki">function unhide_kitchensink( $args ) {
	$args['wordpress_adv_hidden'] = false;
	return $args;
}
add_filter( 'tiny_mce_before_init', 'unhide_kitchensink' );
</pre>

worksforme: <p>
Anyhow, here's my workaround:
</p>
<pre class="wiki">// Have more than one callback attached to the uninstall hook
function add_uninstall_hook($plugin, $callback) {
	// trigger $is_uninstallable_plugin flag
	register_uninstall_hook($plugin, '__return_false');
	add_action('uninstall_' . plugin_basename($plugin), $callback);
}
</pre>
